ValidateBuildResponse
/ Validates the LLM build response
- if %stepResults.steps.Count% is not %goal.Steps.Count%, throw error 'LLM returned %stepResults.steps.Count% steps but goal has %goal.Steps.Count% steps. Steps are lines starting with '- '. Return exactly one result per goal step, with one or more actions per step.'
- foreach %stepResults.steps%, call ValidateStep, item=%step%

ValidateStep
/ Validates a single step from the LLM response
/ keep:true is a shortcut — valid only when the prior .pr has actions for this step
/ and the response has no fresh actions. Other steps must include actions as usual.
- if %step.keep% is true, call ValidateKeptStep
- if %step.keep% is not true, call ValidateBuiltStep

ValidateKeptStep
/ keep:true guard rails: must have prior actions, must not also emit fresh actions
- if %step.actions% is not empty, throw error 'Step at index %step.index% has keep:true but also emitted actions. keep:true means reuse the prior mapping — emit one or the other, not both.'
- if %goal.Steps[step.index].Actions.Count% is 0, throw error 'Step at index %step.index% has keep:true but the prior .pr has no actions. keep:true requires a prior mapping that was offered as @known.'

ValidateBuiltStep
/ Standard validation for fresh-build steps
- if %step.actions% is empty, throw error 'Step at index %step.index% has no actions. Every step must include actions with module and action filled in.'
- builder.validate actions=%step.actions%
